        "## Implementetion of the algorithm\n",
        "In this algorithm I used a fitness of the form: $\\dfrac{1}{1+F(x,y)}$.\n",
        "Therefor the best poin will have a fitness very close to 1.\n",
        "\n",
        "In this example I used a initial population of 10 points that are in a 1x1 square centered on the origin.\n",
        "\n",
        "I used these limits (-1,1)X(-1,1) to have a better visualization but the algorithm works well in larger limits."
      ],

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "start = gap.time.time()\n",
        "while abs(max_fitness-1) > 0.0001:\n",
        "\n",
        "        s, r = gap.ptg(P)   \n",
        "\n",
        "        g += 1 \n",
        "        \n",
        "        listfitness = gap.fitness_all(P)\n",
        "    \n",
        "        points_survivorsC, points_survivors, max_fitness, indexfalse = gap.selection(listfitness, P)\n",
        "        \n",
        "        offspring = gap.crossover(points_survivorsC)\n",
        "        \n",
        "        offspringM = gap.mutation(offspring)\n",
        "\n",
        "        family = gap.integration(points_survivors, offspringM)        \n",
        "        \n",
        "        P = gap.mf(family)\n",
        "        fit_son = gap.fitness_all(P)\n",
        "        \n",
        "        x, y, z, index = gap.selection(fit_son, P)\n",
        "        best_vector = gap.best(P, index)\n",
        "\n",
        "end = gap.time.time()\n",
        "print()\n",
        "best_vector = gap.best(P, index)\n",
        "print(\"Optimized point: \", best_vector)\n",
        "print()\n",
        "print(\"Optimized value: \", gap.F(best_vector[0],best_vector[1]))\n",
        "print()\n",
        "print(\"Number of generations: \", g)\n",
        "print()\n",
        "print(\"Runtime: \", (end-start),\"seg\")\n",
